717584f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 57th Street (West)
717584f-a.text:
176921787 Broadway, west side, south from West 58th to 57th Streets,
showing the General Motors Building occupying the entire block west to
Eighth Ave. This building is today (1937) much higher in height. In the
background, on the south side of West 57th Street is the Fisk Building.
1924.
Wurts Brothers.

717591f.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 57th Street
717591f.text:
Broadway, west side, from 59th to 57th Streets. In the
foreground is the uptown building of the New York Journal.
Below this is the General Notors Building. Ths was origin-
ally built about 1921 as a three-story building, and has
just been remodelled nto a 26-story building.
About 1927.
Herbert Photos, Inc.
